<h1>Outside General Counsel</h1>

<p>Most growing businesses reach a stage where legal questions come up regularly — contracts need to be reviewed, employment issues need guidance, new regulations need to be understood — but where the volume and cost of those needs does not justify a full-time in-house attorney. Outside general counsel is the answer to that gap.</p>

<p>As outside general counsel, I serve as a trusted ongoing legal resource for your business: available when you need guidance, familiar with your company and its context, and able to handle a wide range of day-to-day legal matters without the overhead of a large firm or the cost of hiring a full-time attorney.</p>

<h2>What I Handle</h2>

<h3>Commercial Contracts</h3>
<p>Most business relationships are defined by contracts, and most legal disputes arise from contracts that were poorly drafted, inadequately reviewed, or simply never read carefully before signing. I review, draft, and negotiate commercial agreements — customer contracts, vendor agreements, software licenses, NDAs, service agreements, and partnership arrangements — to ensure that the terms reflect your intentions and protect your interests.</p>

<h3>Employment and Contractor Matters</h3>
<p>Hiring, managing, and separating from employees and contractors involves significant legal exposure, particularly in New York where state employment law is extensive. I advise on offer letters, employment agreements, independent contractor arrangements, restrictive covenants, and separation agreements, helping businesses navigate these issues without creating unnecessary risk.</p>

<h3>Regulatory Compliance</h3>
<p>Many businesses operate in regulated environments without a clear picture of their compliance obligations — data privacy rules, industry-specific regulations, licensing requirements, or state registration requirements. As outside general counsel, I help identify the regulatory landscape your business operates in and develop practical approaches to meeting those obligations.</p>

<h3>Day-to-Day Legal Matters</h3>
<p>Outside general counsel means being available for the legal questions that arise in the ordinary course of business: reviewing a contract before you sign it, advising on a dispute with a vendor or customer, helping you understand what a regulatory notice means, or working through an unusual situation that does not fit a standard category. Having a lawyer who knows your business and is accessible makes a meaningful difference in how quickly and effectively these matters get resolved.</p>

<h2>Engagement Structure</h2>

<p>I work with outside general counsel clients on both a retainer basis — providing a defined level of availability for a monthly fee — and on a project basis for specific matters. The right structure depends on the volume and predictability of your legal needs. I am happy to discuss both options and find an arrangement that works for your business.</p>

